6,'label','en','Label',NULL,NULL,0,0),(27,'enabled','en','Enabled',NULL,NULL,0,0),(28,'form_button_click_documentation','en','Event which fires when the user clicks the button (and the button is enabled).',NULL,NULL,0,0),(29,'on_click','en','On click',NULL,NULL,0,0),(30,'resource_title_database_table_editor','en','Database Table Editor',NULL,NULL,0,0),(31,'resource_documentation_database_table_editor','en','For your web application, manually managing numerous database tables through platforms like phpMyAdmin or by creating individual interfaces for each table can be quite cumbersome. Our system simplifies this process by automatically creating a table editor for you.\n\nThis intuitive editor offers a comprehensive overview of all the rows in a database table, facilitating effortless search, viewing, and modification of data.\n\n- *Sorting Function* Click on the column name to sort (A-Z). A second click sorts in reverse order (Z-A).\n- *Edit* Records can be edited with a click on the edit icon.\n- *Delete* Records can be deleted with a click on the trash bin icon.\n- *Appropriate Form Components like Dropdown, Radio Buttons, Number Input Fields* Utilizing the form generator (form.resource), it creates fitting form components based on defined parameters.\n- *Linked Tables with Dropdown* For instance, the system will conveniently display the corresponding country name in a dropdown menu when a user is associated with a \'country_id\', enhancing user-friendliness.\n- *Search Function Searches Linked Records* The advanced search functionality not only enables queries within connected rows but also makes it easier to explore information linked to these rows. For example, entering \'Canada\' will retrieve all users from Canada, even if the reference in the underlying table is only by \'country_id\'.\n- *Multilingual Display & Search* Moreover, the editor displays the translated value if a table cell contains a translation key, improving data readability and comprehension. 